# Next.js 14 App Router Rules

## Server vs Client Components

### Default to Server Components
Components are Server Components by default. Only add `'use client'` when you need:
- useState, useEffect, useRef
- Event handlers (onClick, onChange)
- Browser APIs (window, localStorage)
- Custom hooks that use client features

### Client Component Directive
```tsx
'use client';
// Must be first line, before imports
```

### Composition Pattern
Keep client components at the leaves:
```tsx
// Server Component (page.tsx)
export default async function Page() {
  const data = await fetchData(); // Server-side fetch
  return <ClientComponent data={data} />;
}
```

## File Conventions

### Special Files
- `page.tsx` - Route page (required)
- `layout.tsx` - Shared layout
- `loading.tsx` - Loading UI (Suspense)
- `error.tsx` - Error boundary (must be client)
- `not-found.tsx` - 404 page

### Route Groups
Use `(groupName)` for organization without affecting URL:
```
app/
  (auth)/
    login/page.tsx    → /login
  (main)/
    visualizer/page.tsx → /visualizer
```

## Data Fetching

### In Server Components
```tsx
// Direct fetch in component (no useEffect)
async function Page() {
  const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data');
  return <div>{data}</div>;
}
```

### Cache Control
```tsx
// Revalidate every 60 seconds
fetch(url, { next: { revalidate: 60 } });

// No cache
fetch(url, { cache: 'no-store' });
```

## API Routes

### Route Handlers
```tsx
// src/app/api/example/route.ts
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from 'next/server';

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  return NextResponse.json({ data: 'value' });
}

export async function POST(request: NextRequest) {
  const body = await request.json();
  return NextResponse.json({ received: body });
}
```

## Metadata

### Static Metadata
```tsx
// In page.tsx or layout.tsx
export const metadata = {
  title: 'Page Title',
  description: 'Page description',
};
```

### Dynamic Metadata
```tsx
export async function generateMetadata({ params }) {
  return { title: `Track: ${params.id}` };
}
```

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

❌ Don't use `getServerSideProps` or `getStaticProps` (Pages Router)
❌ Don't use `useRouter` from `next/router` (use `next/navigation`)
❌ Don't put `'use client'` on every component
❌ Don't fetch data in useEffect when you can do it server-side
❌ Don't use `<a>` tags - use `<Link>` from `next/link`

## Redirects

```tsx
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation';

// In Server Component
if (!session) {
  redirect('/login');
}
```

## Navigation

```tsx
'use client';
import { useRouter } from 'next/navigation';

const router = useRouter();
router.push('/visualizer');
router.replace('/login');
router.back();
```
